04:12.607 --> 04:16.152
- Who's the writer?
- Who'd you think?

04:37.882 --> 04:40.760
Glucose...

04:40.927 --> 04:42.637
...plus oxygen...

04:44.555 --> 04:49.936
Carbon dioxide plus water.

04:51.854 --> 04:54.232
You can clearly see here
that the chemicals

04:54.398 --> 04:56.818
are currently out of balance.

04:56.984 --> 05:00.446
Your task will be
to alter the molar ratios

05:00.613 --> 05:03.282
in order to make the chemicals balance

05:03.449 --> 05:07.745
before and after the combustion
reaction has occurred.

05:12.375 --> 05:15.127
Wouldn't you say that was so,
Mr Curtis?

05:17.129 --> 05:19.048
Ian?

05:19.215 --> 05:20.967
Come on, stop messing.

05:21.133 --> 05:23.052
Uh, Mr Curtis?

05:30.017 --> 05:31.477
What?

05:35.648 --> 05:37.150
Sorry, sir.

05:41.821 --> 05:43.447
Who have we got today, then?

05:43.614 --> 05:45.366
Mrs Brady.

05:46.534 --> 05:50.079
- We done her before?
- Don't think so.

05:50.246 --> 05:53.499
Let's hope she's got
a sympathetic doctor.

05:55.376 --> 05:59.130
I mean, I like
me neighbours, don't get me wrong.

05:59.297 --> 06:02.717
Mind you, the stink of some of them.

06:02.884 --> 06:05.803
I tell you, they don't wash
or don't know how to.

06:06.762 --> 06:09.432
Stink, stink, stink.

06:10.224 --> 06:12.059
Stink to high heaven of piss.

06:12.226 --> 06:15.855
Mrs Brady, please can I use
your toilet, please?

06:16.022 --> 06:17.690
'Course you can, love.

06:18.483 --> 06:22.028
- Second on the left, down the hall.
- Thank you.

06:23.446 --> 06:25.114
Where was I?

06:25.281 --> 06:26.991
