07:07.865 --> 07:09.909
Oh, here we go. Who's that?

07:10.076 --> 07:12.203
Stop it now! Stop it.

07:15.331 --> 07:16.791
- Hi.
- Hi, Nick.

07:16.958 --> 07:19.585
Nick, yeah. Hi.

07:21.212 --> 07:22.922
- Ian.
- Hi.

07:23.089 --> 07:24.632
Hi.

07:24.799 --> 07:28.177
Oh, wow, a dog. What's her name?

07:28.344 --> 07:30.304
- Tess.
- Hello, Tess.

07:30.471 --> 07:33.057
Come around to speak to, you know...

07:33.224 --> 07:36.060
See if she wants to... for a bit.

07:36.227 --> 07:39.647
- Debbie.
- Debbie, yeah. Yeah.

07:40.273 --> 07:42.525
Debbie. Hi.

07:42.692 --> 07:46.154
- Hi.
- She's gorgeous. Debbie, hi.

07:46.320 --> 07:49.615
Hi. Do you want to come in?

07:53.369 --> 07:54.579
Hi.

07:55.371 --> 07:56.581
Hi.

08:09.719 --> 08:12.388
<i>My heart leaps up when I behold</i>

08:12.555 --> 08:14.348
<i>A rainbow in the sky</i>

08:16.225 --> 08:18.728
<i>So it was my life began</i>

08:19.770 --> 08:22.231
<i>So is it now I am a man</i>

08:23.608 --> 08:26.569
<i>So it be when I shall grow old</i>

08:27.361 --> 08:29.071
<i>Or let me die</i>

08:30.323 --> 08:32.991
<i>The child is the father of the man</i>

08:33.951 --> 08:36.578
<i>And I could wish my days to be</i>

08:37.621 --> 08:41.583
<i>Bound each to each by natural piety</i>

08:52.220 --> 08:55.431
- Did you write that?
- Wordsworth.

10:22.977 --> 10:24.437
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

10:28.065 --> 10:30.735
- I'm really excited for this.
- Yeah. Same here.

10:30.902 --> 10:33.654
Never really into Bowie before,
you know, but...

10:39.035 --> 10:40.703
It's a shame Nick couldn't come.

10:42.455 --> 10:44.123
He did say I could go out with you.

10:44.290 --> 10:47.960
He said it was all right.
As long as I looked after you.

10:48.711 --> 10:50.296
Did he now?

10:52.632 --> 10:56.636
Well, I didn't want him thinking we were
going behind his back or anything.

10:57.762 --> 11:00.056
That's a bit presumptuous,
don't you think?

11:01.599 --> 11:03.142
Why?

11:03.309 --> 11:05.436
I might not have wanted
to go out with you.

11:05.603 --> 11:08.314
- Go over there.
- All right.

11:23.204 --> 11:25.832
<i> I wish I were a Warhol silkscreen</i>

11:25.998 --> 11:27.667
<i>Hanging on the wall</i>

11:27.834 --> 11:31.128
<i>Or little Joe or maybe Lou</i>

11:31.295 --> 11:32.964
<i>I'd love to be them all</i>

11:33.840 --> 11:36.259
<i>All New York City's broken hearts</i>

11:36.425 --> 11:38.427
<i>And secrets would be mine</i>

11:39.137 --> 11:40.972
<i>I'd put you on a movie reel</i>

11:41.139 --> 11:44.142
<i>And that would be just fine</i>

12:13.171 --> 12:14.922
I think we should get married.

12:18.134 --> 12:19.677
Are you asking?

12:21.971 --> 12:23.681
You're mine.

12:24.390 --> 12:26.476
Irretrievably.

12:28.060 --> 12:30.813
- Am I now?
- Yeah.

12:32.648 --> 12:34.192
And you know it.

13:25.493 --> 13:27.745
Ian?

13:27.912 --> 13:29.372
I've got a brew for you.

13:34.001 --> 13:35.461
Ian?

13:48.141 --> 13:49.267
All right, lads?

13:49.433 --> 13:51.102
- All right.
- All right, mate.

13:52.520 --> 13:54.397
It's a bit empty in here tonight.

13:54.564 --> 13:56.691
- Tony Wilson's over there.
- Who?

13:57.275 --> 13:59.610
Posh bloke from Granada TV.

13:59.777 --> 14:02.947
- Oh, yeah.
- One day he'll be recognising me.

14:03.114 --> 14:06.325
- You'll have to be out a bit more.
- Yeah.

14:06.993 --> 14:08.452
Been a bit busy.

14:08.619 --> 14:10.997
Getting married, finding a house.

14:11.164 --> 14:12.582
Sounds like fun.

14:13.875 --> 14:17.420
- How's the band?
- Yeah. Not bad.

14:17.587 --> 14:19.922
It's not particularly good
either, is it?

14:21.883 --> 14:25.094
No. We're pretty shite.

14:25.261 --> 14:28.473
Be a lot less shite if we could find
a singer who could sing.

14:33.186 --> 14:36.105
I'm really looking forward
to seeing this lot tonight.

14:36.272 --> 14:39.442
Apparently they tear up the stage
and kick off mid-set.

14:40.902 --> 14:44.280
- All right?
- Gotta go.

14:44.447 --> 14:47.074
- Take it easy.
- See you soon, Ian.

14:48.993 --> 14:51.871
- Embarrassed of me or something?
- No.

14:55.416 --> 14:57.919
- He's all right, him, isn't he?
- Yeah.

14:58.085 --> 15:00.671
A bit tall, bit odd, but yeah.

15:34.872 --> 15:37.792
So you're really
looking for a singer, then?

17:18.851 --> 17:21.813
So, what do you like doing, Colin?

17:21.979 --> 17:24.065
Watching telly.

17:24.232 --> 17:29.487
- Apart from watching telly?
- Hmm, having breakfast, lunch and tea.

17:30.613 --> 17:32.698
Food? Well, that's a start.

17:32.865 --> 17:35.201
There's plenty ofjobs
that involve food.

17:35.368 --> 17:36.577
And watch telly.

17:36.744 --> 17:40.164
- So you like food and watching telly?
- That's right.

17:41.207 --> 17:42.500
Well...

17:42.667 --> 17:45.795
There's a job here working
at Knutsford Cinema

17:45.962 --> 17:48.589
behind the hot dog counter.
How does that sound?

17:48.756 --> 17:51.884
- I do not like hot dogs!
- OK.

17:52.051 --> 17:54.595
Well, should we give 'em
a ring anyway?

18:02.228 --> 18:04.397
The colour scheme is fuckin' brown

18:04.564 --> 18:05.982
Everywhere in chicken town

18:06.149 --> 18:09.610
The fuckin' pubs are fuckin' dull
The fuckin' clubs are fuckin' full

18:09.777 --> 18:11.612
Of fuckin' girls and fuckin' guys
With fuckin' murder in their eyes

18:11.779 --> 18:14.282
A fuckin' bloke gets fuckin' stabbed
Waitin' for a fuckin' cab

18:14.448 --> 18:17.201
You fuckin' stay at fuckin' home
The fuckin' neighbours fuckin' moan

18:17.368 --> 18:19.871
Keep the fuckin' racket down
This is fuckin' chicken town

18:23.875 --> 18:25.918
I'm a bit nervous, me.

18:27.336 --> 18:29.589
Just with it being recorded
and all that.

18:32.133 --> 18:34.635
I mean, we're actually
gonna be on a record.

18:34.802 --> 18:36.971
I can play it at my gran's
and everything.

18:40.475 --> 18:42.643
How about you, Hooky?
You nervous or what?

18:42.810 --> 18:44.479
Am I fuck, man?

18:47.482 --> 18:50.610
- What about you, Ian?
- This is just the start.

18:53.946 --> 18:55.072
Steven?

18:57.325 --> 18:59.035
No.

19:03.080 --> 19:05.750
The fuckin' pies are fuckin' old
The fuckin' chips are fuckin' cold

19:05.917 --> 19:08.544
The fuckin' beer is fuckin' flat
The fuckin' flats have fuckin' rats

19:08.711 --> 19:11.589
The fuckin' clocks are fuckin' wrong
The fuckin' days are fuckin' long

19:11.756 --> 19:15.051
It fuckin' gets you fuckin' down
Evidently chicken town

19:15.218 --> 19:16.677
Thank you. Good night.

19:22.600 --> 19:24.477
Right, Warsaw, we're on.

19:24.644 --> 19:28.189
Fuckin' hell! Who's opened the ham?
You lot nervous or what?

19:36.864 --> 19:38.991
The next band of the night, folks:

19:39.158 --> 19:43.371
Warsaw!

19:51.629 --> 19:53.798
You all forgotten Rudolf Hess?

21:28.935 --> 21:30.770
Ian, it's 400 pound.

21:34.148 --> 21:36.067
Are you sure you want to do this?

21:36.234 --> 21:38.152
I know, but...

21:38.319 --> 21:40.571
The band are gonna pay us back.

21:44.659 --> 21:46.118
OK.

21:52.250 --> 21:54.126
Let's have a baby.

21:58.131 --> 21:59.423
OK.

22:22.446 --> 22:24.323
Four hundred quid.

22:28.578 --> 22:30.204
What are you lot called again?

22:30.371 --> 22:33.166
We were Warsaw.
Now we're Joy Division.

22:33.332 --> 22:36.169
Excuse me, but what happened
to Slaves of Venus?

22:36.335 --> 22:37.837
OK.

22:38.546 --> 22:41.424
- All right. Joy Division's good.
- Joy Division, eh?

22:41.591 --> 22:43.509
What's all that about?

22:44.093 --> 22:47.763
It's the name of a brothel German
soldiers used during World War II.

22:49.599 --> 22:52.602
Well, whatever. Studio's yours.

22:57.064 --> 22:59.817
And it folds up to hold the record.

23:02.111 --> 23:03.404
Have a look.

23:11.913 --> 23:13.831
Yeah, it's good that, Bernard.

23:15.208 --> 23:16.959
Thought-provoking.

23:18.419 --> 23:21.047
That's right. Her name's Corrine Lewis.

23:24.258 --> 23:26.260
<i>Is 2.45 Thursday all right?</i>

23:29.305 --> 23:31.808
OK, then, Mr Mathers,
she'll see you then.

23:32.850 --> 23:34.227
Bye.

23:35.019 --> 23:37.814
Done. He sounds keen.

23:49.784 --> 23:51.244
I'll get some water.

23:53.788 --> 23:58.209
<i> When you're looking at life
in a strange new room</i>

23:59.377 --> 24:01.087
<i>Maybe drowning soon</i>

24:02.213 --> 24:05.174
<i>Is this the start of it all?</i>

24:09.178 --> 24:11.264
I'd never stand for that.

24:12.849 --> 24:14.559
What?

24:14.725 --> 24:17.353
Being called something like
"the Buzzcocks".

24:18.396 --> 24:20.481
What are you on about?

24:20.648 --> 24:24.110
I don't know. I don't mind the Buzz,
but calling themselves Cocks.

24:24.277 --> 24:26.279
I don't get it.

24:26.445 --> 24:29.198
They're not calling themselves
the Cocks, are they?

24:29.365 --> 24:31.659
They're calling themselves
the Buzzcocks.

24:32.827 --> 24:35.705
Still got the word "cock" in it, though.

24:35.872 --> 24:38.457
Just saying I wouldn't stand for it,
that's all.

24:39.834 --> 24:44.130
<i> They were the Buzzcocks.
If you didn't know, well, now you do.</i>

24:44.297 --> 24:47.175
<i>- As you'll soon know about these lot...
- That's us!</i>

24:47.341 --> 24:50.261
<i>... a Manchester band called
Joy Division. This is an EP,</i>

24:50.428 --> 24:53.222
<i>An Ideal for Living.
And that wraps it up for tonight.</i>

24:53.389 --> 24:57.226
<i>Keep the music coming in. Next week
we have The Clash, live in the studio.</i>

24:57.393 --> 24:59.645
We've just been on telly, lads.

24:59.812 --> 25:02.440
So is Tony Wilson a fan,
then, or what?

25:02.607 --> 25:04.066
That was bollocks.

25:05.109 --> 25:07.570
He didn't even say if he liked it
or anything.

25:07.737 --> 25:10.698
- 'Course he liked it.
- Well, how do you know?

25:12.700 --> 25:15.578
He waved it
in front of camera like that.

25:15.745 --> 25:18.873
Forget the record.
He's got to put us on.

25:26.589 --> 25:27.882
Hiya.

25:28.049 --> 25:29.509
There he is.

25:30.843 --> 25:33.471
Um, just orange juice, please.

25:33.638 --> 25:35.223
Go on, tell him.

25:43.022 --> 25:44.357
OK, how are you?

25:44.524 --> 25:47.193
You're gonna go out there,
it's all gonna be fine.

25:50.154 --> 25:52.657
You're not up there having a wank, OK?

25:52.824 --> 25:54.283
Think.

26:00.122 --> 26:03.543
You're a twat, you are.
You're a bastard.

26:03.709 --> 26:04.836
Am I? Why is that?

26:05.002 --> 26:07.213
Because you haven't
put us on television.

26:09.423 --> 26:13.010
Well, then, you'll be the next band
I'll put on, darling.

26:14.470 --> 26:17.223
Fuckin' right we're going on
before your band, twat!

26:17.390 --> 26:19.559
Your band ain't even
a real fuckin' band.

26:19.725 --> 26:21.894
- Fuck off.
- Hooky'll do your head in.

26:22.061 --> 26:23.938
Fuck off!

27:19.452 --> 27:22.580
That was superb, that, lads.
It really was.

27:23.331 --> 27:25.374
I've not seen a reaction like that

27:25.541 --> 27:28.461
since George Best got kicked out
for blasting a bouncer.

27:28.628 --> 27:30.755
I know how you can be better...
like that.

27:32.089 --> 27:34.842
- Go on, then.
- Simple. You employ me.

27:35.009 --> 27:36.677
You play, I manage.

27:36.844 --> 27:40.598
We all get stinkin' rich and go buy
fuckin' great big houses in Cheshire.

27:40.765 --> 27:42.558
- Job's a good 'un.
- And who are you?

27:42.725 --> 27:45.144
Rob Gretton. I already manage
a couple of bands.

27:45.311 --> 27:48.105
But they couldn't sniff the sweat
round your bollocks.

27:48.272 --> 27:50.650
You lot are somethin' else.
I hold my hands up.

27:50.817 --> 27:53.653
I am a believer in Joy Division.
Fuckin' hallelujah.

27:53.820 --> 27:55.863
I'm also resident DJ here,

27:56.030 --> 27:59.659
which means I know anyone of any
music biz use anywhere in this city.

27:59.826 --> 28:03.287
I'll have you lot signed within
the month. In fact, I guarantee it.

28:03.454 --> 28:05.915
We've already got a manager,
haven't we, lads?

28:06.082 --> 28:07.834
- Who's that, then?
- Fuckin' me.

28:08.835 --> 28:10.670
- What's your name, mate?
- Terry.

28:10.837 --> 28:12.296
- Terry what?
- Terry Mason.

28:12.463 --> 28:15.633
Terry Mason. Tez.
You mind if I call you Tez?

28:16.384 --> 28:19.887
Tez, you know jack shit about this
business. Wanna know how I know?

28:20.054 --> 28:21.848
'Cause I haven't heard of you.

28:22.014 --> 28:25.101
I bet you haven't even got
a fuckin' telephone, have you?

28:26.102 --> 28:28.104
Didn't think so. How will you book gigs

28:28.271 --> 28:30.565
and cut deals without a phone,
you daft cunt?

28:30.731 --> 28:32.483
No offence. I call everyone that.

28:33.609 --> 28:36.612
Look, I've got to pack up my gig.
Ring me.

29:07.226 --> 29:09.812
Rob's Records, Rob speaking.

29:10.605 --> 29:13.900
All right, Ian. Yeah, good, yeah.

29:19.489 --> 29:21.741
Well, that's fuckin' brilliant, Ian.

29:24.619 --> 29:26.496
Well, I'll speak to you later, then.

29:27.288 --> 29:28.331
Fine, I understand.

29:28.498 --> 29:31.542
But you've got to sign with Factory.
This isn't an issue.

29:31.709 --> 29:35.296
We're a fresh and exciting label,
you're a fresh and exciting band.

29:35.463 --> 29:39.425
And, most importantly, we both fly
the flag for the Republic of Manchester.

29:39.592 --> 29:42.053
- Don't give a fuck about that.
- I'm a royalist.

29:42.220 --> 29:45.097
- And I suppose they're Nazis as well.
- We're not Nazis.

29:45.264 --> 29:48.059
<i>- What about the money?
- It's 50l50 on the profits.</i>

29:48.226 --> 29:51.687
You own all the publishing rights
and can walk away at any time.

29:51.854 --> 29:54.649
- You serious?
- Rob...

29:54.816 --> 29:57.944
I don't fuck about with talent
I want to work with.

29:58.569 --> 30:02.073
I'll even sign the contracts in my
own blood if it'll make you happy.

30:02.240 --> 30:03.825
We'll speak later, then.

30:06.577 --> 30:10.289
Now remember, we are live,
so no swearing or they will cut you off.

30:10.456 --> 30:12.375
- What about "arse"?
- What?

30:12.542 --> 30:15.837
- Is "arse" a swear word?
- "Arse", yes. It's a swear word.

30:16.003 --> 30:17.797
- No, it's not.
- Bernard,

30:17.964 --> 30:20.800
out there I know
"arse" isn't a swear word.

30:20.967 --> 30:25.513
Here, in TV land,
"arse" is most definitely a swear word.

30:25.680 --> 30:29.058
Trust me, I know
all about swearing and TV.

30:29.225 --> 30:32.436
I'm a master of knowing
when I can and when I can't.

30:32.603 --> 30:35.398
What about "big dog's cock"?
Can you say that?

30:39.402 --> 30:40.611
No.

30:44.240 --> 30:47.160
Seeing as how this is
the first television programme

30:47.326 --> 30:50.204
which brought you the
first appearances from everyone

30:50.371 --> 30:53.249
from The Beatles to the Buzzcocks,
we like to think we bring you

30:53.416 --> 30:56.294
the most new and interesting sounds
in the North-West.

30:56.461 --> 30:58.921
They're called Joy Division,
a Manchester band

30:59.088 --> 31:03.259
except for the guitarist who comes from
Salford. A very important distinction.

31:03.426 --> 31:04.969
<i>This is called Transmission.</i>

33:56.557 --> 33:58.434
I can't believe you did it.

34:00.728 --> 34:02.730
Must have lost about half a pint.

34:02.897 --> 34:04.899
Shows he's serious, though.

34:05.066 --> 34:07.985
How you feelin', Tony?

34:08.152 --> 34:10.237
I've felt better.

34:10.822 --> 34:14.617
Hold on. You spelled Morriss wrong.
It's supposed to be double S.

34:14.784 --> 34:18.036
Tony, you're gonna have to add
another S to this, kid.

34:18.204 --> 34:19.288
Do I have to?

34:19.455 --> 34:23.000
It's not very professional to spell
the drummer's name wrong, is it?

34:37.931 --> 34:40.016
Job's a good 'un. Thanks, Tony.

34:41.768 --> 34:43.396
So...

34:44.272 --> 34:46.482
...I can officially announce
to the press

34:46.649 --> 34:48.693
Joy Division have signed with Factory?

34:48.860 --> 34:52.487
